Histopathological analysis of BALB/c mouse PCLTS by H & E staining showed that uninfected lung tissue slices maintained normal tissue architecture with no evidence of tissue damage up to 5 days of culture (Fig. 1
). In infected PCLTS, at 24 h after infection, there was an increase in lymphocytes in areas where bacilli were located (Fig. 2
). Mycobacteria infected PCLTS showed a mild inflammatory response characterized by the presence of lymphocytes, macrophages and multinucleated cells.
